MIME::Lite::HT::HTML
====================

Perl module to create HTML mail with MIME::Lite and HTML::Template. 
This module provide easy interface to make MIME::Lite object with HTML formatted mail.

You can read a nicely formatted version of the documentation for this module online:

    https://metacpan.org/pod/MIME::Lite::HT::HTML


INSTALLATION

You should be able to install this using your usual method for installing
modules from CPAN. If you don't have one, have a look at:

    http://www.cpan.org/modules/INSTALL.html


DEPENDENCIES

This module requires some other modules and libraries.
See Makefile.PL for a detailed list. If you are going to install
via cpan shell or PPM, you don't have to care about.


